        <h2>Why neighborhood associations matter</h2>
        <p>Neighborhood associations give residents a way to stay informed, raise concerns together, and connect with City Hall and other parts of White Plains. They are the building blocks of WPCNA and an important part of civic life in the city.</p>

        <p>WPCNA supports residents who want to organize their neighborhoods. Whether you are starting from scratch, reviving a dormant group, or looking to make an existing association more effective, this handbook is a good place to start.</p>

        <h2>About the handbook</h2>
        <p>WPCNA hosted its first annual neighborhood workshop on March 11, 2025. The session walked through the practical steps of organizing a neighborhood association in White Plains: building a contact list, setting a regular meeting cadence, working with the City, and connecting with other associations through WPCNA.</p>
        <p>The materials below come from that workshop. They are shared as a reference and starting point. Feel free to adapt them for your own neighborhood.</p>

        <h3>Workshop slides &mdash; March 11, 2025</h3>
